cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new approach to improve the performance of Quicksort, which is a well-known sorting algorithm in computer science. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper discusses the implementation of the proposed algorithm and compares it with other sorting algorithms, which involves programming and optimization techniques. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper mentions the use of parallelization to further improve the performance of the proposed algorithm. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the practical implications of the proposed algorithm, such as its performance on different types of data and its comparison with other sorting algorithms. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on improving the performance of Quicksort by addressing the issue of branch mispredictions, which is a common performance bottleneck in many algorithms.
